+## Deployment-Level Overrides
+
+You can override OpenAI-like response handling per deployment via `litellm_params.openai_like_behavior`:
+
+```yaml
+model_list:
+  - model_name: opensdk/gemini-3-pro
+    litellm_params:
+      model: kilo/google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview-customtools
+      api_base: os.environ/KILO_API_BASE
+      api_key: os.environ/KILO_API_KEY
+      openai_like_behavior:
+        sanitize_visible_text: true
+        raise_on_empty_tool_response: true
+        empty_tool_response_finish_reasons: ["STOP"]
+        empty_tool_response_status_code: 503
+```
+
+Deployment-level settings override any JSON `special_handling.openai_like_behavior` defaults for that provider.
+
 ### How It Works
 
 1. `json_loader.py` checks `supported_endpoints` for `/v1/responses`
